			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Panopto is a video capture, search, and sharing platform that gives users a powerful way to broadcast, record, and discover expert knowledge. We are transforming how people find and manage multimedia information, from capturing the collected output of the world&rsquo;s top universities to giving corporations a way to share their employees&rsquo; best ideas to letting individual experts reach worldwide audiences. Video search is exploding, and Panopto is helping to turn video into more than just entertainment &ndash; it is rapidly becoming a preferred medium for information delivery.</p>
<p>
	With a worldwide user base of tens of thousands of content creators and millions of viewers, Panopto is young enough to be fun and exciting but mature enough that our &ldquo;garage days&rdquo; are behind us. We&rsquo;re looking for top-flight developers: user interface engineers, systems engineers, video wranglers, and interaction designers who create elegant software - to continue Panopto&rsquo;s momentum in enterprise video and help us extend into the mobile and tablet space. Our engineering team is growing fast, and if you&rsquo;re interested in working on a rapidly evolving system loaded with interesting challenges and hard problems, we want to talk to you. If you want an opportunity unleash your creativity, work with a dedicated, talented, and supportive engineering team, and see your coolest ideas turned into cutting-edge software in the hands of millions of users, Panopto might be the place for you.</p>
<p>
	Panopto was founded in 2007 based on technology developed at Carnegie Mellon University. We are located in the heart of Pioneer Square, the center of Seattle&rsquo;s fast-growing startup community. It&rsquo;s a great place to work.</p>
<p>
	Candidates for full-time engineering positions should have several of the following attributes:</p>
<p>
	Strong proficiency with C++, C#, or Objective C (or all three!)<br />
	Solid fundamentals in multithreaded and message-based programming<br />
	Experience shipping products using core technologies:<br />
	UI Engineers: Cocoa (OSX) or Silverlight/WPF (Win), HTML5, jQuery, strong UI design skills<br />
	Systems engineers: Parallel-processing systems, large-scale database/storage systems, relational databases, LINQ and SQL<br />
	Video Engineers: DirectShow/WMF or QT/QTKit/AVFoundation<br />
	At least one of:</p>
<p>
	BS or graduate degree in Computer Science from a top-tier university and software industry experience<br />
	Two or more years of experience as a software engineer with a major software company (Microsoft, Google, Apple, Amazon, etc)<br />
	Development experience in multiple product cycles with a &ldquo;Joel Test&rdquo;-class organization</p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	<em>Panopto is an Equal Opportunity Employer.</em></p>
