			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Here&rsquo;s the scoop on our company and the job:</strong><br />
Panopto /Pan-ahp&rsquo;-toh/ is a fast-growing startup built on the belief that video has the power to transform the way people learn and communicate.&nbsp; We believe that working with video should be much easier than it is today, so we build software that allows people to record and webcast video from any laptop in just a couple of mouse clicks.&nbsp; We also build a video search engine that people can use to find any word, phrase, or video segment from a library of thousands of videos.&nbsp; Businesses and universities use our software to record and webcast all their video content and presentations, store their videos in the cloud, and then make the videos available on any device.</p>
<p>
We have offices in Seattle, Pittsburgh, and London. This position is based in our Pittsburgh location where we fully enjoy the uniqueness, charm and grit of Pittsburgh&#39;s South Side neighborhood. The Pittsburgh Business Times just ranked Panopto as one of the <a href="http://www.bizjournals.com/pittsburgh/event/57561">Best Places to Work in Western PA</a>! We were also recently profiled in the <a href="http://triblive.com/business/headlines/3075430-74/panopto-technology-burns">Tribune-Review</a>. We&#39;re a pretty close crew here and we are each passionate about our jobs and hope that if you get this job, you will be too! Some other cool things about our corporate office include: unlimited caffeine (coffee and soda) and an arcade machine!</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />
&bull; Develop a comprehensive architectural awareness of a complex, cutting edge software product<br />
&bull; Diagnose nuanced performance issues spanning multiple software components<br />
&bull; Use effective analytical techniques to efficiently resolve tier 3 support incidents in the field<br />
&bull; Interact professionally with customers ranging from high level decision makers to IT staff<br />
&bull; Positively represent the company and develop goodwill in all customer interactions<br />
&bull; Respond to support requests over phone and e-mail using Panopto&rsquo;s support ticket system<br />
&bull; Prioritize support tickets and exercise individual judgment&nbsp; based on issue severity<br />
&bull; Manage the ticket escalation process and work closely with engineering team in reporting and tracking software bug resolution<br />
&bull; Write and maintain product documentation/FAQ&rsquo;s/support materials</p>
<p>
<strong>Required Skills:</strong><br />
&bull; Expert troubleshooting and problem solving skills<br />
&bull; Excellent verbal and written communications skills<br />
&bull; Strong Windows/Mac OS/browser troubleshooting knowledge<br />
&bull; Hardware maintenance / troubleshooting<br />
&bull; Strong experience with Windows server 2008, IIS, Windows Media Services, and Microsoft SQL 2005/2008<br />
&bull; Track record of successfully managing technical-client relationships.</p>
<p>
<strong>Preferred Skills:</strong><br />
&bull; Software testing experience<br />
&bull; Video production and editing experience<br />
&bull; Strong knowledge of web and video applications including Silverlight and QuickTime</p>
<p>
<strong>Education/Experience:</strong><br />
&bull; BS Computer Science or MIS<br />
&bull; 3-5 years of client facing support services experience</p>
<p>
<br />
<em>Panopto is an equal opportunity employer</em></p>
]]></description>
